00:18:36,532 --> 00:18:38,626
我敢猜是新奥尔良
New Orleans, if I was to venture.

195
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:41,746
我们抵达之后 便会被带到市场
After we arrive, we'll be put to market.

196
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:43,539
然后嘛...
And beyond that...

197
00:18:44,415 --> 00:18:46,935
我想既然沦为奴隶 也就没什么别的结果了吧
Well, I suppose once in a slave state, there's only one outcome.

198
00:18:47,043 --> 00:18:47,714
不
No.

199
00:18:47,877 --> 00:18:49,877
约翰 我这么说不是为了让你发无名火的
I don't say that to give you empty agitation, John.

200
00:18:49,879 --> 00:18:51,631
对于你们来说是这样
For y'all, there ain't nothing but that.

201
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:53,265
但我可不是被绑架的
But John wasn't kidnapped.

202
00:18:53,424 --> 00:18:55,847
我是被用来抵债的 仅此而已
John's just being held as debt, that's all.

203
00:18:56,010 --> 00:18:57,933
主人还清他的债务我就得救了
Master pay his debt and John be redeemed.

204
00:18:58,095 --> 00:18:59,575
小子 我们的主人不会来救我们的
Boy, our masters will not come for us.

205
00:18:59,722 --> 00:19:01,724
我为大家感到抱歉 但事实如此
John is sorry for y'all, but that's how it be.

206
00:19:01,891 --> 00:19:03,734
不管你们去哪儿 都没我的事
Where you're going, you're going without John.

207
00:19:05,770 --> 00:19:07,113
- 妈妈  - 兰德尔!
- Mama!  - Randall!

208
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:09,858
妈妈!
Mama!

209
00:19:11,609 --> 00:19:13,407
你还好吗?
Are you all right?

210
00:19:14,028 --> 00:19:15,450
你还好吗?
Are you all right?

211
00:19:17,281 --> 00:19:18,703
谢天谢地
Thank you, God.

212
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:22,411
来 起床了
Come on. Get up.

213
00:19:22,745 --> 00:19:24,292
- 我说了 起来了!  - 不 别...
- I said, get up!  - No, don't...

214
00:19:24,455 --> 00:19:26,378
我不想听你废话! 到院子里去
I don't want to hear you talk! Get in the yard.

215
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:27,587
别对我孩子这样!
Not my children!

216
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:31,095
一惊一乍什么 只是次短途旅行而已
Ain't no need for all that. Just taking a little trip, that's all.

217
00:19:31,754 --> 00:19:33,347
坐在船上的时候
Don't want to frighten the children

218
00:19:33,464 --> 00:19:35,091
可不想吓着孩子吧?
over a little boat ride, do you?

219
00:19:35,257 --> 00:19:36,930
我的主人会还清债务的
John's master gonna pay his debt.

220
00:19:37,093 --> 00:19:38,094
排好队!
Line up!

221
00:19:38,219 --> 00:19:39,445
我的主人会还清债务的!
His master gonna pay his debt!

222
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:47,941
你们连个屁都不许放!
I don't want to hear a word out of none of you!

223
00:19:48,938 --> 00:19:50,281
一个也不行
Not a one.

224
00:20:03,411 --> 00:20:04,879
好了 走吧
All right, come on.

225
00:20:06,414 --> 00:20:08,291
走吧
Move. Come on.

226
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:11,377
孩子 来 走吧
Come on, child. Come on.

227
00:20:11,544 --> 00:20:13,046
跟着你妈妈
Follow your mama.

228
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:14,271
来吧 孩子
Come on, boy.

229
00:20:14,296 --> 00:20:15,356
上台阶
Up these stairs.

230
00:20:15,381 --> 00:20:17,634
从马车上下来
Get down out of that wagon. Come on.

231
00:20:18,259 --> 00:20:19,636
走吧 动作快!
Come on. Move it!

232
00:20:20,136 --> 00:20:21,479
走吧!
Let's go!

233
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:22,980
往上 上台阶
Up, up, up the stairs.

234
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:25,770
走吧
Come on, let's go.

235
00:20:30,271 --> 00:20:31,773
动作快点!
Come on, move it!

236
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:33,691
好了 接着走
All right, come on.

237
00:20:35,568 --> 00:20:37,741
嘿 你 起来
Hey, you. Get up.

238
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:39,822
在这儿坐下
Sit down, right there.

239
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:43,166
来
Come on.

240
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:46,583
这儿 坐下就好
Right there. Just sit down.

241
00:21:22,865 --> 00:21:25,084
都高兴点 别郁郁寡欢的
Cheer up and don't be so cast down.

242
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:39,428
要是想活下去 尽可能少当出头鸟
If you want to survive, do and say as little as possible.

243
00:21:40,758 --> 00:21:45,138
不要告诉任何人你的真实身份 也不要告诉任何人你会读会写
Tell no one who you really are and tell no one you can read and write.

244
00:21:47,223 --> 00:21:50,242
除非你想成为棺材里的黑鬼
Unless you want to be a dead nigger.

245
00:22:05,741 --> 00:22:07,334
现在可以闭嘴了吧
Now keep your mouth shut.

246
00:22:15,084 --> 00:22:16,927
我说咱们该跟他们斗
I say we fight.

247
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:19,422
船员并不多
The crew is fairly small.

248
00:22:20,256 --> 00:22:22,608
要是他们考虑周到的话 他们很可能火力充足
Were it well planned, I believe they could be strong-armed.

249
00:22:22,633 --> 00:22:24,510
区区三个人不可能跟整个船上的对着干
Three can't go against the whole crew.

250
00:22:25,636 --> 00:22:27,638
这儿其他人都是黑奴
The rest here are niggers.

251
00:22:27,972 --> 00:22:29,349
地地道道的黑奴
Born and bred slaves.

252
00:22:29,515 --> 00:22:31,768
黑奴是不会反抗的
Niggers ain't got no stomach for a fight.

253
00:22:31,934 --> 00:22:33,277
一个都不会
Not a damn one.

254
00:22:33,435 --> 00:22:37,235
我只知道 要是被运到那里...
All's I know, if we get where we're traveling...

255
00:22:37,648 --> 00:22:39,070
我们不如死了算了
we'll wish we'd died trying.

256
00:22:39,233 --> 00:22:41,702
不要意气用事
Survival's not about certain death,

257
00:22:41,819 --> 00:22:44,322
只有低调行事才能活下去
it's about keeping your head down.

258
00:22:47,283 --> 00:22:50,127
几天之前 我还在家里...
Days ago, I was with my family...

259
00:22:51,662 --> 00:22:53,460
和家人在一起
in my home.

260
00:22:54,999 --> 00:22:57,343
但现在一切都没了
Now you tell me all is lost.

261
00:22:59,461 --> 00:23:02,681
"别告诉任何人自己的真实身份" 这样就能活命了?
"Tell no one who I am." That's the way to survive?

262
00:23:05,926 --> 00:23:07,974
我要的不只是活命
Well, I don't want to survive.

263
00:23:09,513 --> 00:23:12,642
而是生活
I want to live.

264
00:24:41,397 --> 00:24:43,070
真羡慕
Better off.

265
00:24:44,024 --> 00:24:45,571
太羡慕他了
Better than us.

266
00:25:02,584 --> 00:25:03,836
怎么没看到他
I don't see him.

267
00:25:04,003 --> 00:25:04,720
克莱门斯!
Clemens!

268
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:06,717
- 克莱门斯・瑞!  - 主人!
- Clemens Ray!  - Master!

269
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:08,097
- 克莱门斯!  - 瑞老爷!
- Clemens!  - Master Ray, sir!

270
00:25:08,257 --> 00:25:09,509
瑞老爷!
Master Ray!

271
00:25:09,675 --> 00:25:10,796
谁是管事的?
Who's in charge here?

272
00:25:10,926 --> 00:25:11,927
我是船长!
I'm the captain!

273
00:25:12,094 --> 00:25:13,266
我是乔纳斯・瑞先生
I'm Mr. Jonus Ray.

274
00:25:13,429 --> 00:25:15,022
我的律师这有份证明...
My solicitor has documentation...

275
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:17,933
黑奴克莱门斯・瑞是我的财产
verifying the negro known as Clemens Ray is my property.

276
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:20,444
我可没听说过这件事
I know nothing of this arrangement.

277
00:25:20,602 --> 00:25:22,454
立刻将他归还
You are ordered to return that property

278
00:25:22,479 --> 00:25:24,231
否则你将面临盗窃罪起诉
immediately or be charged with thievery.

279
00:25:25,441 --> 00:25:26,693
放了他!
Free him!

280
00:25:29,611 --> 00:25:30,737
主人
Master.

281
00:25:30,904 --> 00:25:32,702
瑞老爷
Master Ray, sir.

282
00:25:34,116 --> 00:25:35,083
克莱门斯!
Clemens!

283
00:25:35,242 --> 00:25:36,442
- 克莱门斯!  - 把他带回去!
- Clemens!  - Get him back!

284
00:25:36,577 --> 00:25:37,954
克莱门斯!
Clemens!

285
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:39,621
克莱门斯!
Clemens!

286
00:25:40,539 --> 00:25:41,381
克莱门斯!
Clemens!

287
00:26:47,689 --> 00:26:49,083
帕克先生
Mr. Parker.

288
00:26:49,108 --> 00:26:52,408
诺瑟普先生 诺瑟普夫人
Ah, Mr. Northup. Mrs. Northup.

289
00:26:52,653 --> 00:26:54,701
所罗门 请允许我给您介绍一款新式领巾
Solomon, could I interest you in a new cravat?

290
00:26:54,863 --> 00:26:56,173
从法国来的百分百丝绸
Pure silk, by way of the French.

291
00:26:56,198 --> 00:26:58,872
我们想买一个新旅行袋 我夫人出门用
We're in need of a fresh carryall for my Mrs.'s travels.

292
00:26:59,034 --> 00:26:59,876
不买别的
Nothing more.

293
00:27:00,035 --> 00:27:01,708
年关将近
The year has passed already.

294
00:27:01,870 --> 00:27:03,180
您又要去桑迪山出差了?
Off to work at Sandy Hill again?

295
00:27:03,205 --> 00:27:04,047
没错
I am.

296
00:27:04,206 --> 00:27:05,549
有一款正合适
I have just the thing.

297
00:27:05,707 --> 00:27:07,380
和您的风格非常相配...
Something to suit your style...

298
00:27:07,543 --> 00:27:10,012
而且很结实 40英里来回绝对没问题
and yet sturdy enough for the 40-mile round trip.

299
00:27:10,170 --> 00:27:11,171
挺不错的
It's beautiful.

300
00:27:11,338 --> 00:27:12,260
多少钱?
At what price?

301
00:27:12,381 --> 00:27:13,348
我们买了
We will take it.

302
00:27:13,507 --> 00:27:16,636
孩子们 快过来看看爸爸给我买了什么
Children, come see what you father has just purchased for me.

303
00:27:16,802 --> 00:27:18,363
先生 稍等一下 这就过去
One moment, sir, and you'll be assisted.

304
00:27:18,470 --> 00:27:20,188
- 帕克先生  - 什么事?
- Mr. Parker.  - Sir?

305
00:27:20,347 --> 00:27:21,564
价钱能不能再商量一下
If we could discuss the price.

306
00:27:21,723 --> 00:27:23,350
不好意思 所罗门 不好意思 诺瑟普夫人
Oh, forgive me, Solomon. Forgive me, Mrs. Northup.

307
00:27:23,517 --> 00:27:25,565
有客人来了 欢迎您 先生
A customer waits. Welcome, sir.

308
00:27:25,727 --> 00:27:27,570
随便看吧 但是小心钱包
Shop well, sir, but mind your wallet.

309
00:27:27,729 --> 00:27:29,530
请别在意那位先生说的
Pay no attention to this gentleman's nonsense.

310
00:27:29,648 --> 00:27:30,740
贾斯珀!
Jasper!

311
00:27:32,234 --> 00:27:34,032
很抱歉打扰了 先生
My regrets for the intrusion, sir.

312
00:27:34,403 --> 00:27:36,076
没关系
No intrusion.

313
00:27:39,908 --> 00:27:41,376
过得愉快 先生
Good day, sir.

314
00:27:41,869 --> 00:27:43,041
您也愉快
Good day.

315
00:27:43,203 --> 00:27:44,921
贾斯珀 出来
Jasper, out.

316
00:27:53,088 --> 00:27:55,341
很好 很好
Very good. Very good.

317
00:27:55,716 --> 00:27:58,265
点一下名 艾来萨!
Let's see, here. Eliza!

318
00:27:59,595 --> 00:28:01,893
听到名字站起来 艾来萨
Stand up when you hear your name. Eliza.

319
00:28:02,764 --> 00:28:03,606
莱西!
Lethe!

320
00:28:07,019 --> 00:28:07,690
约翰
John.

321
00:28:09,438 --> 00:28:10,690
奥伦
Oren.

322
00:28:11,940 --> 00:28:13,112
普莱特
Platt.

323
00:28:16,028 --> 00:28:17,120
普莱特
Platt.

324
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:21,742
站起来
Stand up.

325
00:28:23,702 --> 00:28:25,124
你符合了条件
You fit the description given.

326
00:28:25,287 --> 00:28:26,630
我叫你的名字 你为什么不站起来?
Why didn't you answer when called?

327
00:28:26,788 --> 00:28:28,040
我不叫普莱特
My name is not Platt.

328
00:28:28,207 --> 00:28:29,049
我叫...
My name...

329
00:28:31,376 --> 00:28:33,094
你就叫普莱特
Your name is Platt.

330
00:28:35,297 --> 00:28:37,470
船长 把这些黑奴带到我的车上
Captain, get these niggers to my cart.

331
00:28:50,145 --> 00:28:51,317
嗯
Mmm.

332
00:28:59,613 --> 00:29:00,830
快走
Move.

333
00:29:04,418 --> 00:29:06,178
在后屋为您准备的这些
I believe I have something very much

334
00:29:06,203 --> 00:29:07,796
我相信会令您很满意的
to your liking in the back room.

335
00:29:07,955 --> 00:29:09,673
请跟我来
Follow me, please.

336
00:29:09,831 --> 00:29:12,675
好了 你们可以随便看...
Yes. Now, inspect them at your leisure...

337
00:29:12,834 --> 00:29:17,681
但我希望你们注意一下年轻的埃兹拉
but I ask you to pay particular regard to young Ezra here.

338
00:29:17,839 --> 00:29:19,091
健壮的四肢
Incredibly sound limbs.

339
00:29:19,258 --> 00:29:21,352
我都没见过体格这么好的
I have never seen anything quite like him.

340
00:29:21,510 --> 00:29:24,354
还有这家伙 很不错吧? 嗯?
And this marvelous creature. Can you believe it? Mmm?

341
00:29:24,513 --> 00:29:26,186
她会是个出色的女仆
She'll make a fine lady's maid.

342
00:29:26,348 --> 00:29:27,520
您说是吧?
Madam?

343
00:29:27,849 --> 00:29:29,522
请随意挑选吧
So, inspect at your leisure.

344
00:29:29,685 --> 00:29:31,983
尽情地看 这边还有点心
Take your time. Help yourself to refreshments.

345
00:29:32,145 --> 00:29:35,149
先生们 有感兴趣的吗? 嗯?
Gentlemen, what catches your fancy here? Hmm?

346
00:29:35,649 --> 00:29:36,650
这个小伙子?
This boy? Yes?

347
00:29:36,817 --> 00:29:38,990
张嘴 张大一点
Open your mouth. Open wider.

348
00:29:39,152 --> 00:29:41,530
看吧 他从来都没生过病
Look in there. Never been sick a day in his life.

349
00:29:41,697 --> 00:29:43,340
请允许我介绍一下玛莎
And I call particular attention to Martha.

350
00:29:43,365 --> 00:29:45,834
她做糕点很拿手
She is an excellent pastry cook.

351
00:29:45,993 --> 00:29:47,711
啊 福特先生
Ah, Mr. Ford.

352
00:29:48,161 --> 00:29:50,459
见到您真荣幸 您有感兴趣的吗?
Splendid seeing you, sir. What catches your fancy?

353
00:29:50,622 --> 00:29:52,670
这个小伙子? 他很结实
This lad? He's very brawny.

354
00:29:52,833 --> 00:29:55,644
普莱特和艾来萨一共多少钱?
How much for the ones Platt and Eliza?

355
00:29:55,669 --> 00:29:57,216
好吧
Ah, yes.

356
00:29:57,629 --> 00:29:59,856
普莱特一千美元 哦
A thousand for Platt. Uh... Oh.

357
00:29:59,881 --> 00:30:02,680
这个黑奴可是很有两下子的
This is a nigger of considerable talent, I assure you.

358
00:30:02,843 --> 00:30:04,561
艾来萨七百美元
700 for Eliza.

359
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,393
价格公道
My fairest price.

360
00:30:06,722 --> 00:30:07,894
嗯
Mmm.

361
00:30:08,724 --> 00:30:09,896
用票据付款行吗?
You will accept a note?

362
00:30:10,058 --> 00:30:12,652
求您了 先生 别把我们一家分开
Please, sir. Do not divide my family.

363
00:30:12,811 --> 00:30:14,063
别把我从我的孩子们身边带走
Do not take me unless you take my children.

364
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:15,230
艾来萨! 闭嘴!
Eliza! Quiet!

365
00:30:15,397 --> 00:30:17,117
我一定会对您忠心耿耿的
You will have the most faithful slave in me.

366
00:30:17,274 --> 00:30:18,617
一定会对您忠心耿耿的
The most faithful slave that has ever lived.

367
00:30:18,775 --> 00:30:19,901
求求您别拆散我们
But I beg that you do not separate us.

368
00:30:20,027 --> 00:30:21,074
那个男孩多少钱?
Your price for the boy?

369
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:22,579
艾来萨! 别说了!
Eliza! Stop it!

370
00:30:22,738 --> 00:30:23,910
谁管你哭不哭
I will give you something to cry about.

371
00:30:24,072 --> 00:30:26,245
兰德尔 上前来 过来
Randall, come forward. Come, come, come.

372
00:30:26,408 --> 00:30:28,627
您看到这个男孩多健康了吧?
Now, do you see how fit this boy is?

373
00:30:28,785 --> 00:30:30,037
就像成熟的果实
Like ripe fruit.

374
00:30:30,203 --> 00:30:33,082
能把手杖借我吗? 看这个
May I take your stick a moment? Observe this.

375
00:30:33,248 --> 00:30:35,250
兰德尔 跳起来 跳起来
Randall, jump, jump, jump. Run, run, run.

376
00:30:35,417 --> 00:30:37,590
很好! 再高点
Very good! Higher.

377
00:30:37,753 --> 00:30:38,879
您看到了吧
Now, you see this.

378
00:30:39,046 --> 00:30:42,641
他长大肯定是个壮汉
It's very likely he will grow into a fine beast.

379
00:30:43,884 --> 00:30:45,602
六百美元
600 for the boy.

380
00:30:45,761 --> 00:30:47,263
一口价
Fair and final.

381
00:30:47,888 --> 00:30:49,105
好吧
Done.

382
